<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GEN-WALL-COLUMN-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FINALS ARE FOR THE BIRDS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Don't know who wanted the Los Angeles Lakers in
the NBA grand finale more, the Peacock or the Bird.
</P>
<P>
   ``Well, listenin' to Magic coach that team out there for a
while, we may have a shot at it,'' Larry Legend joked after his
Pacers polished off the Knicks in the Eastern Conference finals.
</P>
<P>
   Listenin' to Magic complain to Ahmad Rashad right before the
fourth quarter about how we ... uh, the Lakers ... were stinkin' it
up against the Blazers, sounds like he still is trying motivational
tactics.
</P>
<P>
   Too bad it won't officially be Bird vs. Magic again in these
Finals. But ya know, deep down, it still will be ...
</P>
<P>
   --If the Lakers go to their Lack-A-Shaq offense against Indy,
they'll get crunched in crunch time.
</P>
<P>
   PhilJax has to know they only have the Blazers' cold
fourth-quarter shootin' to thank for getting 'em to the Finals. The
Pacers (Reggie Miller) won't allow that. ...
</P>
<P>
   --If Bill Walton makes one more reference to Moses Malone. ...
</P>
<P>
   --At last, Bonzi is gonzo. ...
</P>
<P>
   --Tastiest trade rumor involving the knackless Knicks is getting
P. Ewing (aka P.U.-ing) shipped off to Washington (home of G'town)
as some sorta way for MJ to establish credibility. ...
</P>
<P>
   --A Laker-turned-Pacer-returned-Laker Byron Scott could be an
NBA head coach, but Sacramento keeps asking for too much (draft
picks) in return. Which could be a blessing in disguise for the
future King B. ...
</P>
<P>
   --Glad the NCAA finally figured out a way to keep Cal State
Northridge's football team out of the postseason. ...
</P>
<P>
   --Among the 772 players competing today and Tuesday in
qualifiers for the final 86 spots in the U.S. Open golf tournament
field is Carolina Panthers tight end Brian Kinchen (who carries a
plus-1 index). He would be the first pro athlete ever from another
sport to make the tourney. ...
</P>
<P>
   --Todd Hundley will likely throw out his back more times this
year than baserunners. ...
</P>
<P>
   --The longer Steve Young takes, the better his chances of not
comin' back. Which'll only backfire on the 49ers, trying to give
him as much time as possible to get a clear picture in his mind.
...
</P>
<P>
   --And if Eric Lindros ever skates again, he should have his head
examined. ...
</P>
<P>
   --Whatever happened to Kevin Orie? ...
</P>
<P>
   --Someone in Phoenix best make sure Gretz didn't buy into the
C'yotes with some of that funny money left to him by Lompoc
resident Brucie McNall. ...
</P>
<P>
   --One of the reasons Peter Warrick decided to go with Norm Nixon
as his agent - Normie's wife (the lovely Debbie Allen) said she's
willing to choreograph a career in the entertainment biz for the
C'nati Bengals' No.1 draft pick. ...
</P>
<P>
   --The 23-year-old daughter of Roberto Duran - her name being
Irichelle - was supposta be the latest female fight legacy to get
in the ring, but her four-rounder in England over the weekend was
called off because she was running a fever.
</P>
<P>
   Meaning she's got that ``No Mas'' stuff down already.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
