to do, the harder it is to get it to do anything. The same
principle goes for watches. Wind-up watches couldn't calculate the
rate of return on your investment portfolio, but at least they
don't force you to read a manual that would give Stephen Hawking a
headache just to get the time of day. (Cummings, Dayton Daily News)
