<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GADGETS0606-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Digital watches
 &HT;    By James Cumming
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   DAYTON, Ohio _ One principle almost always holds true when it
comes to gadgets of any kind: The more the gadget is able to do,
the harder it is to get it to do anything.
</P>
<P>
   The same principle goes for watches. Wind-up watches couldn't
calculate the rate of return on your investment portfolio, but at
least they don't force you to read a manual that would give Stephen
Hawking a headache just to get the time of day.
</P>
<P>
   Timex, longtime manufacturers of inexpensive watches, has come
up with a digital watch that is actually easy to set and use.
</P>
<P>
   While many digital watches have an array of buttons, knobs and
bars that must be depressed, pulled, twisted or jabbed, the Timex
i-Control crown-set watch line has one button and one ``crown''
like the stem and knob on a traditional wind-up watch.
</P>
<P>
   Crown-set watches offer some of the most popular features of
other digital watches: They keep track of the date, they have a
built-in alarm and they have a night light that makes the watch
face easy to read in the dark.
</P>
<P>
   The digits are nearly half an inch high, so telling the time at
a quick glance is no problem.
</P>
<P>
   It took less than two minutes to set a sample watch with the
correct time, date and an alarm time. The instructions are so
simple that everything you need to know to operate the watch is
scribed on the back of the watch body.
</P>
<P>
   Pull the stem out until it clicks at the halfway point and the
watch tells you you're ready to set the time. Pull the stem until
it clicks at the fully extended point and the watch tells you
you're ready to set the alarm.
</P>
<P>
   Timex i-Control crown-set watches should be available now for a
suggested retail price of $34.95 at stores that carry other Timex
products. If you have trouble finding the watches, contact the
company at (800) 367-8463 or www.timex.com for a retailer near you.
</P>
<P>
   Also new from Timex are a line of i-Control ring-set watches
that offer more features such as stopwatch functions and countdown
timers. But of course, with more features comes more complexity.
</P>
<P>
   Instead of the crown and button that control the crown-set
watches, the ring-set watches have a crown, two buttons and a
movable ring around the face of the watch. Still, they are a little
easier to use than other watches with comparable features.
</P>
<P>
   The ring-set watches come in Ironman Triathlon, Reef Gear and
Expedition styles and sell for $42.95 to $47.95.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
