<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TECH-WEEWEB0606-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Check out the Adventures of GreatKid
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   www.greatkids.com _ Read stories about extraordinary kids who
are inventors, volunteers, sports stars and musicians. There's
12-year-old Daniel in Santa Cruz, Calif., who invented a
``decrinkler'' for dollar bills, an idea inspired by finicky
bill-changing machines at video arcades. Meet Craig, also 12, from
near Toronto, who with 20 friends started a non-profit group called
Free the Children that encourages world leaders to pass laws to
protect children from employers who exploit them. There are now
Free the Children chapters in seven countries. They credit a new
child labor law in Canada to their work. If you know a kid who
should be recognized, the operators of this site would like to hear
from you.
</P>
<P>
   www.fun4children.com _ This is a site of jokes, riddles and
rhymes for kids, by kids. Here's one from Becky of Palm Coast (no
state listed): How do you catch a blue elephant? Answer: With a
blue elephant gun. Question: How do you catch a pink elephant?
Answer: Hold the nose of the pink elephant until he turns blue and
use the blue elephant gun. Other features to the site include
animation of the day, the birthday page, and crafts and activities,
with instructions on how to make such goodies as paper butterflies,
pencil holders and personalized bookmarks.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
