<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Attention all mutantsBy Omar L. Gallaga
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   www.mutantwatch.com _ Are you or someone you know a mutant? It's
a pretty transparent tie-in to the upcoming ``X-Men'' movie, but
this site has a cute premise _ national hysteria about mutants
spawns an anti-mutant Web site. Using this site, you can report
friends as mutants and they'll receive a notification from
mutantwatch.com about their unlucky mutant status.
</P>
<P>
   www.americatakingaction.com _ Cobbled together by ``parents,
teachers and business and community leaders across the nation,''
this site is a comprehensive education site listing schools all
over the country. It features massive amounts of information on
schools broken down by state and township. Along with addresses and
phone numbers, the site also has events calendars and parent
resource centers.
</P>
<P>
   www.sylloge.com/5k/ _ Tired of bloated, lumbering Web sites that
take forever to load? This contest, which required entrants to
build an entire self-contained Web site using only five kilobytes
of space, drew an amazing array of sites that used ingenuity to
make up for hard drive space.
</P>
<P>
   www.lyricsworld.com _ If you've ever stayed up late at night,
wondering what in the world Eddie Vedder was mumbling about on the
third Pearl Jam album, here's the place to find out. The site is a
search engine for song lyrics. You can type in a keyword and it
will route you along, hopefully to the same song you've got in your
head.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
