<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TECH-PLAYGEAR0606-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    More juice for your Game Boy
 &HT;    By Staff Reports
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   AUSTIN, Texas _
</P>
<P>
   A must-have peripheral for Nintendo's Game Boy Color, The Game
Buddy ($20; www.bti.ca) from Battery Technologies, Inc., is an
add-on rechargeable battery pack for the puny little hand-held game
device. It supplies nearly 24 hours of constant play with each
charge. It purports a whopping 2,000 hours of total storage
capacity and fits snugly to the base of the Game Boy Color where it
interfaces with the AC adapter port. It remains attached even while
charging. The Game Buddy also acts as a night light when it's
recharging, a beacon of hope in a dark sleepless night. The unit
also gives the Game Boy significantly more heft than some portable
game users are accustomed to, but don't be a wimp _ you've got 24
hours of recuperation and gaming time for your efforts. It's cool.
</P>
<P>
   DAZZLING, DIRT-FREE DIMPLES
</P>
<P>
   And from the ``what will they think of next and shouldn't we
shoot them before they do?'' files comes the BallButler ($90;
www.golfballbutler.com), a washing accessory for avid golfers who
happen to own their own electric golf carts. Mounted just about
anywhere on one's cart (fender, basket, drink holder _ No! No! Not
the drink holder!) and drawing power from the cart battery, the
patented BallButler embraces one's filthy whackable orb while a
diminutive 12-volt motor spins it about amongst ``polypropylene
monofilament brushes in a solution of water and detergent leaving
it sparkling clean.'' What more could you want? Someone to hit for
you, maybe?
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
