<P>
   All columns have moved, in the commentary (k) category. If you
have questions or need a resend, please call CoxNet, the Cox News
Service, at 404-526-5456.
</P>
<P>
   SCHUETT-COLUMN _ GIBSONBURG, Ohio _ The weather's been good _
some rain, some sun. The corn is just about as tall as it should be
this time of year, and nobody died last night _ which means there's
not a whole lot to grumble about this morning. The cafe's kind of
quiet _ until Gene walks in _ then it's time to pick on the new
guy. (Schuett, Cox News Service) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LANE-COLUMN _ DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. _ I have not succeeded in
making myself follow the presidential elections. In this, I suspect
I am not so different from most Americans. When you have two
candidates racing to out-moderate each other, they tend to blur
together in people's minds. Both Vice President Al Gore and Texas
Gov. George W. Bush are pursuing reasonableness to an unreasonable
degree. (Lane, Daytona Beach News-Journal) MOVED
</P>
<P>
   KLEINBERG-COLUMN - LONDON - It is a situation in which I often
find myself. No visit to London can be complete without a swing
through that leviathan of a department store, Harrod's.
Particularly to the book department as that is contiguous to the
sewing and needlepoint department to which my wife is devoutly
drawn despite the fact that the inventory there hasn't changed in a
dozen years. (Kleinberg, Cox News Service) MOVED
</P>
