   &UR; ENTERTAINMENT/ARTS (e) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   AUTHOR-GRENOBLE (Greenfield, Mass.) _ Move over J. K. Rowling.
Out in the bucolic hinterland of Western Massachusetts lives a
freckle-faced sixth-grader who is so adept at putting the fruits of
a gifted imagination into words that she recently won a national
writing contest for young authors. By Alison Bass. 1200 words.
PHOTO
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-SUMMER (Undated) _ We gaze upon this year's vacation fare
as vistas of possibility, offering transport to foreign lands, and
even temporary foreign identities, for the armchair traveler. By
Gail Caldwell. 1,800 words.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-JOHNSON (Undated) _ ``Le Mariage,'' by Diane Johnson, is
