<P>
   INTERNATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   CLINTON_ President Clinton meets with Ukraine President Leonid
Kuchma, who is expected to announce that the Chernobyl power plant,
scene of the world's worst nuclear accident in 1986, will be shut
down this year with U.S. financial assistance. Earlier, Clinton
told Russian legislators today that partnership despite differences
is the right course for both their nations, though it is ``not
guaranteed that we will be allies.'' (Deans, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   ISRAEL-GEORGIA _ More than a dozen police from Atlanta and
around Georgia are in Jerusalem to share tips with Israeli
counterparts on fighting terrorism, drug smuggling and common
crime. (Kaplow, Cox News Service). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   NATIONAL
</P>
<P>
   LEWIS-DEAL _ ATLANTA _ NFL star Ray Lewis would be sentenced to
12 months' probation for his part in a post- Super Bowl brawl in
Buckhead that left 2 men dead. (Rankin/Torpy, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). Developing. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (a) General News and (s) Sports categories.
</P>
