   LEWIS-IMPACT _ ATLANTA _ What does the Lewis plea mean to Paul
Howard politically and to Reginald Oakley and Joseph Sweeting,
freedom-wise, and the families and friends of Jacinth Baker and
Richard Lollar, justice-wise .(Rankin/Torpy, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   COMMANDMENTS-JUDGE _ Alabama voters will decide Tuesday whether
to make Roy Moore, the judge who became famous for hanging the Ten
Commandments in his courtroom, the Republican nominee for chief
justice of the state Supreme Court. (Manuel, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WWII MEMORIAL _ Veterans to Save the Mall hold a news conference
to express opposition to the proposed World War II Memorial, saying
the memorial is too large and intrusive for its planned space.
(Garcia, Cox News Service). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   SCOTUS-DAVIDIANS _ In a unanimous decision, the U.S. Supreme
Court reverses the lengthy firearms sentences for five Branch
Davidians and orders U.S. District Judge Walter Smith of Waco to
resentence them to shorter terms. The decision means that juries
must determine as an element of the offense what types of weapons
defendants use, not a judge at sentencing. (Witherspoon, Waco
Tribune-Herald). Mugs of Smith, defendants available.
</P>
<P>
   MICROSOFT _ WASHINGTON _ Government prosecutors file a final
brief requested by the judge in the antitrust case. (Glass, Cox
News Service). 20.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Moving in (w) Washington and (f) financial categories.
</P>
<P>
   WAN location Atlanta, category Business, subcategory Technology.
</P>
<P>
   SCOTUS-GRANDPARENTS _ WASHINGTON _ Dealing a setback to
grandparents, a divided U.S. Supreme Court ruled Monday that
grandparents do not have a constitutional right to visit their
grandchildren against parent's wishes. (Lipman, Cox News Service).
</P>
<P>
   WAN location Atlanta, category National, subcategory U.S.
Government
</P>
