<P>
   &UR; IT'S A MAD, MAD, MAD, MAD WORLD: DON'T RUSH INTO MISSILE
DEFENSES &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ABM-MISSILE-RETHINK-ECONOMIST &LR;  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (UNDATED) _ When U.S. President Bill Clinton meets with Russian
President Vladimir Putin beginning June 4, he will propose to amend
the 1972 Anti-Ballistic Missile (ABM) treaty to allow limited
land-based defenses against a limited missile attack, not from
unthreatening Russia, but from hostile regimes, such as North
Korea's. Clinton and Putin should look to their defenses in a
spirit of cooperation, rather than confrontation. It is too big a
decision to be rushed. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (ATTN: Commentary Editors) &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (TIMELY for June 4 Putin-Clinton summit)
