<SLUG> BC-TOYSRUS-STREET </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TOYSRUS.COM SETS EXPANSION 
</HEADLINE>
   (Stock quote in last graf does not reflect market close)  
 By CAROLYN KOO   
 c. 2000 NYTimes.com/TheStreet.com   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Toysrus.com, the online offshoot of Toys R Us (TOY:NYSE), said
Monday that it will expand, opening new offices in New Jersey and
the San Francisco Bay area by the end of the summer.
</P>
<P>
   The move comes as other Internet-based toy retailers have
shuttered their operations.
</P>
<P>
   The new East Coast office of Toysrus.com will be located in Fort
Lee, N.J., a short distance from New York City, while Toys R Us,
the second-largest toy retailer behind Wal-Mart Stores (WMT:NYSE),
is based further from New York City, in Woodcliff Lake, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   The Fort Lee facility will occupy 46,000 square feet and hold up
to 240 employees by 2001.
</P>
<P>
   A lease in San Francisco will be finalized in the next few
weeks, the company said.
</P>
<P>
   The move by Toysrus.com comes in the face of recent industry
downsizing, as some Internet companies aim for those rare
commodities of profitability and continued funding. For instance,
just last month, toysmart.com, an online retailer of educational
games and toys majority-owed by Disney (DIS:NYSE), closed its
three-year-old operation after using up much of its cash without a
source of replenishment. Also in May, Viacom's (VIA:NYSE)
RedRocket.com, another Web-based toy store, went out of business.
</P>
<P>
   Shares of Toys R Us were up 2 percent, or 5/16, to 16 3/4 in
midday Monday trading.
</P>
<P>
   (For use by clients of The New York Times News Service)
</P>
</TEXT>
