<P>
   FBN-LEWIS-TRIAL (Undated) _ Baltimore Rams linebacker Ray Lewis
pleads guilty to a misdemeanor count of obstructing justice and, in
exchange, murder charges are dropped against the player. The plea
agreement came as Lewis was standing trial for murder in Atlanta in
the stabbing deaths of two players outside a Super Bowl party last
January. Under the deal, Lewis was sentenced today to a year of
probation. What now has to be resolved is what penalties he will
face from the National Football League. By Thomas George.
</P>
