<P>
   RACE IN AMERICA
</P>
<P>
   The New York Times is publishing a series of articles titled,
``How Race Is Lived in America.'' The following is a list of photos
which have moved with the first three installments of the series.
</P>
<P>
   The photos have moved as part of the New York Times Photo
Package. Photo clients have automatically received these photos via
AP's PhotoExpress or may download them from either the Wieck Photo
Database in Dallas at 972-392-0888 or from NYTPhotos on Newscom at
305-448-8411. Non-clients can make individual purchases at a
special price of $100 per photo by calling (888) 603-1036 or
212-556-4204.
</P>
