   (NYT101) ATLANTA -- June 2, 2000 -- RACE-CHURCH-1 -- Howard
Pugh, who owns a concrete company, at a job site with Johnny Clark
and Donald Roberts. He draws a distinction between his black church
friends and his black employees, whom he calls ``the boys.'' (James
Estrin/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT102) ATLANTA -- June 2, 2000 -- RACE-CHURCH-2 -- The Pughs,
and the Burches at the Assembly of God Tabernacle in Decatur, Ga.,
where blacks make up almost half the congregation. (James
Estrin/The New York Times)
