</P>
<P>
   RUSSIA-CLINTON (Moscow) _ William Jefferson Clinton's legacy
looked secure in Ukraine with 30,000 adoring people greeting him.
But just hours earlier, Russia's parliament sat stony faced as he
lectured it. The truth is, Clinton's last lap here shows just how
ambiguous he has been to this land. By David Filipov and Brian
Whitmore. 1200 words.
</P>
<P>
   IRELAND-ANALYSIS (Belfast) _ Northern Ireland Assembly gets back
together after several months, but the sounds of discord bode ill
for the rocky marching season ahead. By Kevin Cullen. 750 words.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; NATIONAL (a) &LR;
</P>
<P>
   COURT-GRANDPARENTS (Undated) _ Supreme Court affirms the primacy
of parents in decisions about their children's lives, in a ruling
that advocates for children, grandparents, and homosexuals hailed
as a milestone in legal recognition of the changing composition of
American families. By Adam Pertman. 1300 words.
</P>
<P>
   TERRORISM-REPORT (Washington) _ A suggestion by a congressional
