u f BC-LADN-BUDGET &LR;      06-05 0136
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following story for
use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of Tuesday, June
6, and thereafter. For questions about stories, contact Stewart
Slavin at the Daily News, (818) 713-3701.
</P>
<P>
   SALEM-COX (Camarillo, Calif.) _ Salem Communications Corp. said
Monday it has entered into an asset exchange agreement with Cox
Radio Inc. to exchange Houston radio station KKHT-FM for the
transmitting facility WALR-FM in Atlanta. Salem will now have 72
stations, including 53 in the top 25 markets. By Chris Sieroty.
</P>
<P>
   LLOYD-COLUMN (Los Angeles) _ Let the hire beware. Daily News
columnist Ken Lloyd, Ph.D., a specialist in organizational
behavior, answers readers' questions on workplace ethics and
relationships.
</P>
</TEXT>
