   SCOTUS-DEATH (Washington) _ The Supreme Court orders a new
sentencing hearing for convicted Texas killer Victor Saldano after
state prosecutors conceded that the jury was given a list of
reasons, including his ethnicity, for why he would be a continuing
danger. By STEVE LASH.
</P>
<P>
   COURT-GRANDPARENTS (Washington) _ Wading into the complexities
of modern American families, the Supreme Court rules that parents
generally have the right to decide whom their children may visit,
including grandparents. In a 6-3 decision, the court strikes down a
Washington state judge's order under a law that allowed ``any
person'' _ a non-relative as well as a grandparent _ to seek
visitation rights with children. By MARK HELM. (Already filed.)
