<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEAH-PERSONALS-SFCHRON </SLUG>
  
 
 PERSONALS: The Local Cultural Scene 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &UR; (Eds: This story also moved in the ``a'' national news file.) &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; By LEAH GARCHIK &QC;  &LR; 
 &UR; c.2000, San Francisco Chronicle &LR;  &QC; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &UR; King Abdullah II &LR;  and  &UR; Queen Rania &LR;  of Jordan, who were in San
Francisco over the weekend, took an entourage of 20 or so to the
Metreon on Saturday, June 3, to see ``Big Momma's House.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Carol Carr &LR;  knows that ``Sophie's Choice,'' the name of one
of the specialties at an Oakland crepery, refers to the name of the
chef, but still, novelist  &UR; Bill Styron &LR; 's definition of ``Sophie's
Choice'' _ that ``the Nazis will let me take only one of my two
little children with me and the other will be killed; which one
shall I choose?'' _ makes it an unappetizing allusion.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Alicia Silverstone  &LR; gave the costume designers for ``Love's
Labour's Lost'' a hard time, she told George magazine, because she
insisted they substitute synthetic fibers for the feather, silk and
fur they'd planned on her wearing. She also told the magazine that
she had filmed a TBS documentary about elephants in Zimbabwe with
floppy-trunk syndrome.
</P>
<P>
   _ Having seen a sign that said, ``I Lost 40 Pounds in Two Weeks.
Free samples,''  &UR; Richard Ault &LR;  of San Francisco doesn't want to
know what the samples are.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Nelson Mandela &LR;  has gotten the  &UR; Duchess of York &LR;  to help
raise money for schools in South Africa, reports the Times of
London. Mandela, apparently no scholar of royal family affairs, was
so taken with Fergie when he met her last summer, says the
newspaper, that he said, ``The queen must be beaming with pride.''
</P>
<P>
   _ The engagement ring  &UR; Donald Trump  &LR; gave  &UR; Marla Maples &LR;  fetched
$110,000 at auction on Friday, June 2.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Wesley Snipes &LR;  wants to turn a 300-acre farm in Georgia into
a training camp for security guards, but the Putnam County Planning
and Zoning Board is insisting that the land is meant for
agriculture.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Jesse Ventura &LR;  will play himself in an episode of ``The Young
and the Restless.'' The Minnesota governor will tape the appearance
next week during a visit to California.
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; JUST HUM IT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   The following is a smattering of  &UR; Pat Boone &LR; 's words to
``Chariots of Fire,'' as Wireless Flash says are sung in his new
CD, ``In a Symphonic Mood'':
</P>
<P>
   ``We search for a meaning/ We strive for a goal/ We drink from
life's fountain/ To fill up our soul.''
</P>
<P>
   &LR;  &QL; 
 &UR; WHO SAID WHAT &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; ``Wealth is just another word for change. Wealth comes
directly &LR; 
 &UR; from innovation and upheaval. Ask yourself, What kind of person &LR; 
 &UR; spends all of his time thinking about how to change things? The &LR; 
 &UR; answer is: a person who is not happy with things as they are. &LR; 
 &UR; People who aren't happy with the way things are tend never to be &LR; 
 &UR; happy with things as they are, even after they have changed &LR; 
 &UR; them. They have a gift for remaining dissatisfied.'' &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Michael Lewis &LR; , author of ``The New New Thing'' (W.W. Norton;
$25.95), a book about the high-tech explosion, explains why rich
people are grumpy, in a Town &AMP; Country special issue on the new
affluence.
</P>
