right, and Stf. Sgt. Earnest Williams see race standing in the way
of their ambitions. (Ozier Muhammad/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT302) FORT KNOX, Ky. -- June 5, 2000 -- RACE-MILITARY-2 -- In
a military that calls itself colorblind, two sergeants see race
standing in the way of their ambitions. Doing situps for Sgt. Harry
Feyer, a recruit had trouble taking the discipline seriously.
(Ozier Muhammad/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT303) FORT KNOX, Ky. -- June 5, 2000 -- RACE-MILITARY-3 -- In
a military that calls itself colorblind, two sergeants see race
standing in the way of their ambitions. Sgt. Earnest Williams
drilling the Fourth Platoon on family day at Fort Knox. (Ozier
